      <h3 class="divheading sm-above-large">Academics</h3>
      <p class="h5 l-1-5">Excelling in academics, Dr.Manjunath did his Bachelors and Master Degree in Music securing First Rank and Four Gold Medals from the University of Mysore. Subsequently, University of Mysore awarded him Ph.D for his scholarly thesis on Violin. University of Mysore accolades him as one among the alumni having the distinction and Stature of Eminence contributing to the society significantly. He is nominated the Cultural Ambassador by the University of Mysore during its centenary celebrations.</p>
      <p class="h5 l-1-5">Dr. Manjunath, a distinguished Professor – Department of Music at The University of Mysore, has successfully guided many research students in the Ph.D program. Innumerable scholars and researchers from Europe and US, on Fulbright fellowship have studied under his Supervision. His methodology of analyzing different playing techniques & other intricate Music – Performing Arts have been followed by many reputed research scholars and musicologists.</p>
      <p class="h5 l-1-5">Dr. Manjunath has the distinction of being invited for special Conferences, Presentations, Workshops & Concerts at some of the  World’s Top Universities including, The MIT- USA, Oxford University, University of Chicago, University of North Texas, IIT, The Kansas State University, University of Osaka Japan, University of Princeton, Griffith University – Australia, Texas A & M University – USA, University of Central Oklahoma, The University of Utrecht School of Arts – Netherlands.</p> 
    </div>        
  </div>
  <div class="row gap-above-large">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6">
      <h3 class="divheading">Cultural Ambassador</h3>
      <p class="h5 l-1-5">Violin Concerts of Dr. Manjunath have been featured in innumerable Music festivals & conferences all over the world. He is the first Indian violinist to be invited to perform at the Prestigious International Violin Conference held in Sandiego. He is the first ever Indian Musician to perform at the Persian Academy in The Islamic Republic Of Iran. He has performed at highly reputed  World Music festival in Chicago, Bozar Music conference in Belgium, Conservatorium Van Amsterdam and National Centre for Early Music – UK. The Government of India sent him to Slovenia for special Republic Day Concert at the Congress Hall as the Cultural Representative of our country. some of the Top European orchestras like Ictus, Okamoon have repeatedly featured him as a lead Violinist in various concert series in France, Germany, Netherlands. His concert at Reputed Milano Music Festival in Italy was telecasted live across Europe. He was invited to perform at reputed Putra World Trade Centre, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, SAARC summit, Theatre-dala-ville in Paris & Singapore Fine arts.</p> 
      <p class="h5 l-1-5">World renowned BBCand ABC (Australian Broadcasting Corporation) featured him in their special international programs as the Brilliant Musician from India. Innumerable events he has been invited by Indian embassies abroad.  His dexterity in the subject made him one of the Front line Musicians of Indian classical Music. Recently he has been sent for a special Violin concert to Srilanka as a special  Cultural Delegate by Indian Government in connection with 70th Independence day celebrations.</p> 
      <p class="h5 l-1-5">Dr. Manjunath has repeatedly enthralled audiences all over the world in over 30 countries. He is indeed true cultural ambassador of India who continues to preserve and spread the rich cultural heritage of Indian classical music, in all its glory.</p>
